data.text:
'Forced to step back ... ': Congress hits out at Modi 3.0 over lateral entry U-turn; BJP says 'needlessly excited'

timesofindia.com / Aug 21, 2024, 18:27 (IST)

The Congress criticised the Modi government's leadership, pointing out several policy reversals. These included the cancellation of the UPSC lateral entry proposal for IAS positions, withdrawal of the Broadcasting Services Bill, and restoring property indexation benefits. The BJP defended these actions as flexibility and sensitivity to feedback. Both opposition and NDA allies have welcomed these changes.

Bharat Bandh: Protesters try to burn school bus with children on board - Video

timesofindia.com / Aug 21, 2024, 21:35 (IST)

Some protesters in Bihar attempted to set a school bus on fire during the Bharat Bandh on Wednesday. The bandh aimed to demand community-based reservations. Disruptions occurred across railway stations and roads, leading to the arrest of several individuals involved in the protests.

Paytm to sell ticketing business to Zomato in Rs 2,048cr deal

tnn / Aug 22, 2024, 02:06 (IST)

Paytm will sell its entertainment ticketing business, including TicketNew and Insider, to Zomato for Rs 2,048 crore, the company announced. This deal, set to transition over a year, would move around 280 Paytm employees to Zomato. The sale aims to bolster Paytm's balance sheet and refocus on core financial services.

American Airlines passenger bleeds from hair transplant surgery, arrested for refusing to deboard

timesofindia.com / Aug 22, 2024, 00:37 (IST)

​​A Las Vegas couple was arrested from an American Airlines plane after their resistance to deboard the plane when the flight crew asked them to do so as the man was profusely bleeding from his head. The bleeding was because of a hair transplant surgery and the man said he did not have a fresh bandage to cover his head. All passengers had to be deplaned and the flight was delayed as the couple said it they could not fly, no one else would either.

Faceless, fair & friendly: Finance minister's mantra for taxmen

tnn / Aug 22, 2024, 02:08 (IST)

Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman emphasised a faceless, fair, and friendly income tax regime, urging simplification in communication to avoid intimidating taxpayers. She praised the increasing number of first-time tax filers and adoption of the new tax regime. Sitharaman highlighted improvements in refund issuance and stressed the need for proportional enforcement and prioritizing grievance resolution.
